text: Westerkwartier is a municipality in the province of Groningen, the Netherlands. In 2019, 63,031 people lived there. It was created on 1 January 2019 from the former municipalities of Grootegast, Leek, Marum, Zuidhorn and partly Winsum. == References == == Other websites == * Official website Category:2019 establishments in the Netherlands
